1
00:00:00,733 --> 00:00:02,900
Why would I even do that?

2
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:13,400
<i>You really had me
cook pork adobo, I swear.</i>

3
00:00:13,533 --> 00:00:15,767
<i>- What, you're still insisting?
- Mom, Mom, please.</i>

4
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:17,033
<i> She's confused and angry...</i>

5
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:19,133
<i>because of the weight of the
problems she's carrying.</i>

6
00:00:19,267 --> 00:00:20,133
<i> Thank you.</i>

7
00:00:20,267 --> 00:00:21,900
<i> Your support means a lot.</i>

8
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:23,733
<i> I won't give up on Manuel.</i>

9
00:00:23,867 --> 00:00:28,500
<i>I'll stand my ground
that I'm truly Mrs. Cruz.</i>

10
00:00:28,633 --> 00:00:29,733
<i> Dad, Jessica's gone.</i>

11
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:32,067
<i>But Jeff, Coleen,
and I are still here.</i>

12
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,100
<i> Why, Andrea?</i>

13
00:00:33,233 --> 00:00:34,433
<i> What did your mother tell you?</i>

14
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:35,933
<i> That you're hurting yourself?</i>

15
00:00:36,067 --> 00:00:37,567
<i> So he had to go back to you?</i>

16
00:00:37,700 --> 00:00:39,000
<i> And you believed her?</i>

17
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:41,300
<i> What?</i>

18
00:00:41,433 --> 00:00:42,967
<i> Dad, what's really going on?</i>

19
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:52,400
Coleen, don't get me wrong.

20
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:54,367
No malice, okay?

21
00:00:54,633 --> 00:00:56,800
Is it possible something
might develop

22
00:00:56,933 --> 00:00:59,333
between Ma'am Felma
and Sir Noah?

23
00:00:59,467 --> 00:01:00,400
No way.

24
00:01:01,533 --> 00:01:03,300
Come on.

25
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:06,800
Ma'am Felma's been different
lately.

26
00:01:06,933 --> 00:01:10,667
You see how calm she gets
when Sir Noah's around.

27
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:13,567
And she keeps smiling.

28
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:19,333
Didang, that's fine.
At least Mom's distracted.

29
00:01:19,467 --> 00:01:22,667
But I think they're
just friends.

30
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:25,500
They didn't end up together
before.

31
00:01:25,633 --> 00:01:27,867
Why now, when Dad's already
back?

32
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,967
Really? He's back?

33
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:32,233
Didn't he go with someone else?

34
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:34,700
What really happened
to your Dad?

35
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:37,533
He vanished like smoke.

36
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:38,967
Not a word.

37
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:41,133
Not even a goodbye.

38
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:43,633
Not even to me!

39
00:01:45,533 --> 00:01:47,100
Didang?

40
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:49,533
Why would Dad say goodbye
to you?

41
00:01:50,633 --> 00:01:52,233
Just kidding!

42
00:01:52,367 --> 00:01:54,667
Wait, are they dating?

43
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:58,133
I'm confused, I don't get it.

44
00:01:58,267 --> 00:02:01,933
We don't get it, either.

45
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:05,500
That's why I want
to talk to Dad.

46
00:02:06,567 --> 00:02:08,767
I want to know what
the problem is,

47
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:10,900
so he can come home again.

48
00:02:14,733 --> 00:02:17,200
Dad, are you hiding something
from me?

49
00:02:19,033 --> 00:02:20,667
I don't believe this.

50
00:02:22,733 --> 00:02:24,833
Hazel, what is it?

51
00:02:24,967 --> 00:02:26,300
Hazel...

52
00:02:26,433 --> 00:02:28,300
Please, stay out of this.

53
00:02:28,433 --> 00:02:31,333
Leave my daughter alone.
Go, Joel. Take her away.

54
00:02:31,467 --> 00:02:33,067
No. No, no!

55
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:35,867
I'm not leaving until I know
what's going on.

56
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,900
Sweetheart, nothing's going on.

57
00:02:38,033 --> 00:02:40,133
I just went back to Hazel.

58
00:02:40,267 --> 00:02:43,333
Go on. Please, dear,
respect that.

59
00:02:43,467 --> 00:02:45,133
Dad, you're hiding something
from me.

60
00:02:45,267 --> 00:02:46,867
Tell me the truth.

61
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,567
Nothing.

62
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:50,500
This is the truth.

63
00:02:50,633 --> 00:02:51,567
Believe me.

64
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:53,633
This is for your and your
siblings' own good.

65
00:02:53,767 --> 00:02:55,267
So please, go.

66
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,433
No.

67
00:02:56,933 --> 00:02:58,933
I'm not going anywhere unless
you're with me.

68
00:02:59,067 --> 00:03:00,000
Let's go home, Dad.

69
00:03:00,133 --> 00:03:01,900
If I have to drag you, I will.

70
00:03:02,033 --> 00:03:03,767
- Your dad isn't going.
- Dad, let's go!

71
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:06,033
No matter what you do,
he's not going with you!

72
00:03:06,167 --> 00:03:07,633
Hazel, enough!

73
00:03:07,767 --> 00:03:09,333
This is your fault!

74
00:03:09,467 --> 00:03:11,533
What did you do to Dad?
Did you force him?

75
00:03:11,667 --> 00:03:12,700
Threaten him?

76
00:03:13,733 --> 00:03:15,500
Why are you blaming me?

77
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:18,067
You don't know the whole story.

78
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:20,367
Hazel, enough!

79
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:21,667
Dad, what's happening?

80
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,933
What's the truth?

81
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:25,600
What should I know?

82
00:03:25,733 --> 00:03:27,233
Andrea, don't blame Hazel.

83
00:03:27,367 --> 00:03:29,233
She's not at fault.

84
00:03:29,367 --> 00:03:30,500
I made this decision.

85
00:03:30,633 --> 00:03:31,500
Your mother and I.

86
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:33,400
And why, Dad?

87
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:34,667
Why?

88
00:03:36,167 --> 00:03:38,900
Why do you keep deciding
without us?

89
00:03:40,267 --> 00:03:42,800
We're grown-ups now.

90
00:03:42,933 --> 00:03:49,733
Why don't we get a say
in family matters like this?

91
00:03:49,867 --> 00:03:51,033
We're the ones who get hurt

92
00:03:51,167 --> 00:03:53,300
when you decide things
like that.

93
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:57,067
Mom's drinking again.

94
00:03:58,967 --> 00:04:02,000
Coleen still blames herself.

95
00:04:04,433 --> 00:04:06,133
And me, Dad...

96
00:04:06,267 --> 00:04:08,733
I barely got to spend time
with you.

97
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:12,333
And now you're leaving me again?

98
00:04:16,367 --> 00:04:17,333
Dad, please...

99
00:04:17,467 --> 00:04:19,267
don't leave me.

100
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:21,233
Please, let's go home.

101
00:04:21,367 --> 00:04:22,967
Dad, let's go home.

102
00:04:24,367 --> 00:04:26,167
Let's go home, Dad.

103
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:29,133
Please.

104
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:32,433
Andrea, stop being stubborn.
Go now.

105
00:04:32,567 --> 00:04:34,200
No!

106
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:37,067
- Dad, please...
- Sorry if I hurt you, okay?

107
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:39,267
What's done is done.

108
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:42,933
- Let's just accept it. Go home.
- No.

109
00:04:43,067 --> 00:04:44,733
- Dad, you should come with us.
- Joel, take her home.

110
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:47,600
- Don't push me away, Dad!
- Go home!

111
00:04:47,733 --> 00:04:49,400
Dad!

112
00:04:49,533 --> 00:04:51,500
Joel!

113
00:04:51,633 --> 00:04:53,400
Let go of me!

114
00:04:55,167 --> 00:04:56,333
Dad.

115
00:04:57,867 --> 00:04:59,467
No!

116
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,700
Dad!

117
00:05:15,467 --> 00:05:17,267
Andrea, come on. Let's go home.

118
00:05:20,967 --> 00:05:23,367
They're hiding something
from me, Joel.

119
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,367
Dad's hiding something.

120
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:29,000
You heard what Hazel said,
right?

121
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:31,600
And how Dad reacted.

122
00:05:31,733 --> 00:05:33,133
He stopped her from talking.

123
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:37,033
And if Mom was part
of the decision,

124
00:05:38,967 --> 00:05:40,733
then she knows something, too.

125
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:43,533
<i>Jeff, tell me. What do you know?</i>

126
00:05:43,667 --> 00:05:46,233
<i>If you don't, we'll go confront
Mom again.</i>

127
00:05:46,367 --> 00:05:48,367
<i> Hazel hurts herself.</i>

128
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:50,067
<i>She took a lot of sleeping pills</i>

129
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,767
<i>and had to be rushed
to the hospital.</i>

130
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:55,900
And Jeff...

131
00:05:57,733 --> 00:05:59,733
Jeff lied to us.

132
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:05,733
He knew the truth
and didn't tell us.

133
00:06:05,867 --> 00:06:08,367
Andrea, you're overthinking.

134
00:06:09,567 --> 00:06:10,967
Don't think that way.

135
00:06:19,267 --> 00:06:20,500
You know something, too.

136
00:06:21,733 --> 00:06:22,933
Andrea, let's go.
I'll take you home.

137
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:24,133
Let's go home.

138
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:26,800
No, Joel.

139
00:06:28,033 --> 00:06:29,967
Tell me the truth.

140
00:06:32,467 --> 00:06:35,667
Why did Dad go back to Hazel?

141
00:06:36,900 --> 00:06:38,367
What's the reason?

142
00:06:44,967 --> 00:06:46,833
Bro, didn't I tell you
it was a secret?

143
00:06:46,967 --> 00:06:49,000
And you did the one thing
I told you not to do.

144
00:06:49,133 --> 00:06:50,367
You told Andrea.

145
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,867
Bro, I'm really sorry.

146
00:06:52,767 --> 00:06:56,033
I warned you,
I can't lie to your sister.

147
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:57,600
But you can lie to other girls?

148
00:06:57,733 --> 00:07:00,567
Not anymore. I've changed.
I'm decent now.

149
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:03,500
What's so bad about me
knowing it?

150
00:07:03,633 --> 00:07:06,333
Aren't we partners in crime?
What is this?

151
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:09,633
Andeng, if I tell you,
you might slip and tell Coleen.

152
00:07:09,767 --> 00:07:11,867
That's what Mom and I are trying
to avoid.

153
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:15,067
You know what Coleen's going
through.

154
00:07:15,233 --> 00:07:17,700
If she finds out Dad went back
to Hazel

155
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:20,767
so she wouldn't go to jail,
she'll blame herself even more.

156
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:23,400
That's what's happening now.

157
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:25,433
Coleen's blaming herself.

158
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:30,300
She thinks Dad believes
Hazel's claim

159
00:07:30,433 --> 00:07:33,133
that she really pushed Jessica.

160
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:35,967
She even thinks Dad's angry
at her.

161
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:38,067
Exactly.

162
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:40,433
That's what Dad wants.

163
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:42,833
For Coleen to get mad at him...

164
00:07:42,967 --> 00:07:45,700
so it'll be easier
for him to leave.

165
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:52,233
Now I understand how big Dad's
sacrifice is.

166
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:55,767
And Mom's too.

167
00:07:57,367 --> 00:07:59,733
I feel so bad for them, Jeff.

168
00:08:00,867 --> 00:08:04,733
But your mom can't find out
that you know the truth.

169
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:07,633
Then what's this family
even for?

170
00:08:08,933 --> 00:08:12,067
Wouldn't it be better
if we were open?

171
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,300
So we can help each other?
Support each other?

172
00:08:14,433 --> 00:08:15,967
Not drown in secrets.

173
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:17,733
What secret?

174
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:33,133
Sis, what secret are you talking
about?

175
00:08:35,167 --> 00:08:36,867
I...

176
00:08:37,133 --> 00:08:40,967
I went to Hazel's place.

177
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:43,267
Joel just dropped me off.

178
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:45,200
Right.

179
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:46,800
We just came from there.

180
00:08:48,233 --> 00:08:52,167
I wanted to talk to Dad.

181
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:56,133
I feel sorry for you and Mom.

182
00:08:56,433 --> 00:08:58,433
Did he face you?

183
00:08:58,567 --> 00:09:01,367
Did he tell you why he went back
to Hazel?

184
00:09:02,267 --> 00:09:03,033
No.

185
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,200
He didn't talk to me.

186
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:08,167
I didn't even see him.

187
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:11,900
What if I talk to him?

188
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,967
Do you think he'd face you?

189
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:29,400
Jeff, come on...

190
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:33,100
Is this right?

191
00:09:34,433 --> 00:09:37,033
Hiding all this from Coleen?

192
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:53,533
Trust Aunt Felma for now.

193
00:09:53,967 --> 00:09:57,533
If she doesn't want Coleen
to know, just follow her lead.

194
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:00,133
They're still your parents.

195
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:02,067
They know what's best
for all of you.

196
00:10:03,167 --> 00:10:06,100
Thank you for the encouragement,
Joel.

197
00:10:06,233 --> 00:10:07,800
And...

198
00:10:07,933 --> 00:10:11,167
thank you for taking the risk
to tell me the truth.

199
00:10:12,267 --> 00:10:13,267
It means a lot.

200
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:17,100
Andrea, you're not a stranger
to me.

201
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:18,000
All of you.

202
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:19,833
That's why I told your brother,

203
00:10:20,867 --> 00:10:22,700
somehow, you made me a better
person.

204
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:26,933
And I just hate seeing
your family struggling.

205
00:10:27,067 --> 00:10:30,067
Because if my family went
through that,

206
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:33,033
I'd do everything I could
to fix it.

207
00:10:33,167 --> 00:10:35,300
I appreciate everything
you're doing, Joel.

208
00:10:36,467 --> 00:10:37,967
Thank you.

209
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:40,033
What are friends for, right?

210
00:10:40,167 --> 00:10:41,533
Unless...

211
00:10:41,667 --> 00:10:43,933
you're okay with being more...

212
00:10:44,067 --> 00:10:46,567
Looks like it's gonna rain.

213
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:47,833
You should go home.

214
00:10:47,967 --> 00:10:49,600
- No, there are stars out.
- Take care, okay?

215
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:50,367
Okay, fine.

216
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:52,433
Yeah. And hey, don't drive fast.

217
00:10:52,567 --> 00:10:54,133
- Be careful.
- Okay. Bye. Bye.

218
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:13,700
Jeff?

219
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:14,433
Jeff!

220
00:11:14,567 --> 00:11:16,133
Didang, it's open. It's open!

221
00:11:16,267 --> 00:11:19,700
Jeff, we need your help.
It's your mom.

222
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:21,933
- Why? What happened?
- Let's go!

223
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:24,333
Mom!

224
00:11:24,467 --> 00:11:25,600
Mom.

225
00:11:25,733 --> 00:11:28,967
Mom, the water's freezing.
You'll get sick.

226
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:31,267
Mom, come on, that's enough.

227
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,933
Mom!

228
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:38,033
- Mom, please, come on. Mom!
- Mom! Mom! Mom!

229
00:11:38,167 --> 00:11:39,267
Goodness, Mom.

230
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:41,067
We've been trying to stop her,
but she won't listen.

231
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:43,633
Son, come on, let's swim.

232
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:44,867
Swimming at night?

233
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,467
Mom, it's late.
The water's cold.

234
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:47,767
And you've been drinking.
Give me that.

235
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:49,033
Mom!

236
00:11:49,167 --> 00:11:51,967
That's why it's night swimming.
Because you do it at night!

237
00:11:52,100 --> 00:11:53,133
Mom, come here.

238
00:11:53,267 --> 00:11:54,567
- It's cold.
- Mom, please.

239
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:55,833
- You've had too much.
- Come on, it'll spill.

240
00:11:55,967 --> 00:11:58,800
- Ma'am, that's enough!
- Give it here.

241
00:11:58,933 --> 00:12:01,000
- No more. Mom, stop.
- Give it!

242
00:12:01,133 --> 00:12:02,767
- What are you doing?
- You've had too much.

243
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:03,633
No...

244
00:12:03,767 --> 00:12:04,833
Mom!

245
00:12:04,967 --> 00:12:07,000
- Mom!
- What's your problem?

246
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:09,100
I'm just having fun!

247
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,267
What about you, guys?

248
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,100
When you were at the resort,
you were drinking, too.

249
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:14,800
Did I stop you?

250
00:12:16,267 --> 00:12:17,067
Mom.

251
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,133
That's enough.

252
00:12:18,267 --> 00:12:20,933
- Come here. That's enough.
- You'll get sick.

253
00:12:21,067 --> 00:12:24,233
- Come on. Don't be stubborn.
- There, there.

254
00:12:24,367 --> 00:12:25,667
Enjoy.

255
00:12:27,367 --> 00:12:28,367
- Coleen, get that.
- Mom.

256
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:30,767
- Give me the glass, Mom.
- No, no.

257
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:33,167
- Get it, get it.
- Slowly. Mom.

258
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:36,433
- Careful, Ma'am.
- Mom!

259
00:12:36,567 --> 00:12:37,533
Easy, easy.

260
00:12:37,667 --> 00:12:40,067
- Mom.
- Careful, Ma'am.

261
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:41,400
Mom!

262
00:12:41,533 --> 00:12:42,867
Mom!

263
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,600
- Can you do that?
- Put this on.

264
00:12:45,733 --> 00:12:48,400
- Wait, I got it, I got it.
- Mom! Mom! It's cold, Mom.

265
00:12:48,567 --> 00:12:50,433
- Put this on, Mom.
- What? Why are you stopping me?

266
00:12:50,567 --> 00:12:51,800
- What?
- It's just once in a while!

267
00:12:51,933 --> 00:12:53,700
- There.
- You guys are too much.

268
00:12:53,833 --> 00:12:55,767
Mom. Didang, can you tie it,
please? Hold on.

269
00:12:57,067 --> 00:12:59,500
Water. Didang, water, please.

270
00:12:59,633 --> 00:13:02,100
Hey, hey!

271
00:13:02,233 --> 00:13:04,033
What? See? You're freezing now.

272
00:13:04,167 --> 00:13:05,733
That's what you get
for drinking nonstop

273
00:13:05,867 --> 00:13:07,367
when you can't even handle it.

274
00:13:28,033 --> 00:13:29,300
Ma'am, you're so stubborn.

275
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:30,500
Careful.

276
00:13:33,567 --> 00:13:34,200
Okay.

277
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:40,033
Wait, I'll get a towel.

278
00:13:40,167 --> 00:13:42,667
Coleen, get Mom's pajamas.

279
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:46,367
What's happening to Mom?

280
00:13:51,467 --> 00:13:52,767
<i> Mom?</i>

281
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:55,367
<i> Mom, wake up.</i>

282
00:13:57,733 --> 00:14:00,900
<i> We'll wipe you down, Mom.</i>

283
00:14:01,033 --> 00:14:02,767
<i> What time is it?</i>

284
00:14:04,067 --> 00:14:09,600
She was exactly like this
the first time Dad left us.

285
00:14:11,067 --> 00:14:13,567
If only we got to talk to Dad...

286
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:17,167
Maybe he wouldn't have gotten
mad at me.

287
00:14:18,667 --> 00:14:21,067
Maybe Mom wouldn't have been
dragged into this mess.

288
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:30,400
<i>I hurt Andeng's feelings
earlier.</i>

289
00:14:30,567 --> 00:14:31,633
<i> How is she?</i>

290
00:14:37,533 --> 00:14:38,800
Who's that?

291
00:14:38,933 --> 00:14:42,600
Jeff, step out for a bit so we
can change your mom's clothes.

292
00:14:44,033 --> 00:14:44,833
Here you go.

293
00:14:54,633 --> 00:14:57,000
<i>I hurt Andeng's feelings
earlier.</i>

294
00:14:57,133 --> 00:14:58,533
<i> How is she?</i>

295
00:14:58,667 --> 00:15:02,333
<i>Were you able to explain
to her properly why I'm here?</i>

296
00:15:21,367 --> 00:15:22,467
What was that?

297
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:25,100
Oh, just the pillow. It fell.

298
00:15:27,667 --> 00:15:28,733
I'll get it.

299
00:15:28,867 --> 00:15:30,733
No, no. It's fine, I'll get it.

300
00:15:32,767 --> 00:15:34,000
You sure?

301
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:34,800
Yeah.

302
00:15:37,233 --> 00:15:38,733
Why aren't you asleep yet?

303
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:43,333
Coleen's hearing is early
tomorrow, right?

304
00:15:43,467 --> 00:15:45,400
Yeah. I'm going to sleep now.

305
00:15:47,633 --> 00:15:48,367
Good night.

306
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:49,467
Good night.

307
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:16,933
It's taking so long, Attorney.

308
00:16:22,667 --> 00:16:23,300
Timo.

309
00:16:24,433 --> 00:16:25,300
Attorney.

310
00:16:25,433 --> 00:16:26,267
Thank you.

311
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:30,600
Attorney, glad you made it.

312
00:16:30,733 --> 00:16:33,100
Thanks for coming,
Atty. Salazar.

313
00:16:34,067 --> 00:16:37,067
You know my lawyer,
Atty. Briones from PAO, right?

314
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:37,933
Of course.

315
00:16:38,067 --> 00:16:41,000
Attorney Briones from PAO.

316
00:16:41,133 --> 00:16:44,133
You know, Timo,
I shouldn't even be here.

317
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:47,000
But he called me.

318
00:16:49,733 --> 00:16:52,300
Attorney, I asked you to come

319
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:56,167
because I really want you
to personally hear

320
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:57,833
what I have to say.

321
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:04,733
And I want Mrs. Cruz
to hear it, too.

322
00:17:09,167 --> 00:17:10,333
Attorney Briones,

323
00:17:12,933 --> 00:17:16,800
there's something I want
to change in my testimony.

324
00:17:16,967 --> 00:17:18,367
Are you recanting?

325
00:17:22,467 --> 00:17:26,367
Timo, you swore to tell
the truth.

326
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:27,967
What is this now?

327
00:17:28,100 --> 00:17:30,967
You know you can be charged with
perjury for doing that, right?

328
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:33,633
Don't push me.

329
00:17:33,767 --> 00:17:37,567
<i>I can make your life miserable
in here.</i>

330
00:17:41,967 --> 00:17:44,900
I know they can add perjury
to my case.

331
00:17:45,967 --> 00:17:49,833
But my conscience can't take it
anymore.

332
00:17:50,733 --> 00:17:53,133
I need to tell the truth.

333
00:17:54,500 --> 00:17:55,600
What truth?

334
00:17:57,667 --> 00:18:01,433
Coleen didn't push Jessica.

335
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:24,300
Why aren't you dressed yet?

336
00:18:25,933 --> 00:18:28,300
I thought you were coming
with me to Coleen's hearing?

337
00:18:29,567 --> 00:18:31,733
Attorney Salazar just called.

338
00:18:32,933 --> 00:18:34,567
He said he already spoke
to Timo.

339
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:37,467
Manuel, what you wanted has
happened.

340
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,967
Has Timo taken back his
statement?

341
00:18:50,967 --> 00:18:52,967
This came from the court.

342
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:57,367
A copy of Timo Malabanan's
affidavit of recantation.

343
00:18:57,533 --> 00:18:59,067
Recantation?

344
00:19:01,067 --> 00:19:03,333
He's withdrawing his original
statement.

345
00:19:04,433 --> 00:19:07,400
He said it wasn't true
that you pushed Jessica.

346
00:19:09,267 --> 00:19:13,233
Does that mean Coleen won't go
to jail anymore?

347
00:19:13,367 --> 00:19:17,800
Well, there's a big chance,
Jeffrey.

348
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:22,567
Timo's statement was the only
evidence against Coleen.

349
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:25,133
So what's next, Attorney?

350
00:19:25,267 --> 00:19:27,933
What do we need to do?

351
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:32,433
All we have to do now is wait
for the court's decision.

352
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:40,200
Why would Timo take back his
statement?

353
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:42,633
What happened?

354
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,567
That's a copy of the court's
dismissal order.

355
00:20:03,733 --> 00:20:05,367
Dismissed?

356
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:08,167
So the case won't push through
anymore?

357
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:09,767
Coleen won't go to jail?

358
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:11,100
Yes.

359
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:15,633
Apparently, the court accepted
Timo Malabanan's recantation.

360
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:17,433
Thank goodness.

361
00:20:20,133 --> 00:20:22,167
Aren't you going to say
anything, Mrs. Cruz?

362
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:27,167
Shouldn't you be furious right
now and telling me to...

363
00:20:28,833 --> 00:20:32,033
Mrs. Cruz, we can file
a motion to...

364
00:20:32,167 --> 00:20:33,033
No need.

365
00:20:34,367 --> 00:20:36,500
That's unbelievable.

366
00:20:37,733 --> 00:20:39,100
Before,

367
00:20:39,233 --> 00:20:42,267
you'd charge head-on whenever
something favored Coleen.

368
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:45,500
Why is it all of this seems
nothing to you now?

369
00:20:45,633 --> 00:20:49,700
And Timo's recantation...

370
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:53,133
Shouldn't you be reacting
by now?

371
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:55,767
Unless...

372
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,700
you did something again.

373
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:02,733
What would I even do, Attorney?

374
00:21:02,867 --> 00:21:05,000
I don't know.

375
00:21:05,133 --> 00:21:12,033
Mrs. Cruz, did you pay Timo
to withdraw his statement?

376
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:20,600
Why would I do something
that would only make me lose?

377
00:21:20,867 --> 00:21:23,833
Please, instead of throwing
accusations,

378
00:21:23,967 --> 00:21:27,333
why don't you just admit
you didn't do your job?

379
00:21:27,467 --> 00:21:29,067
That's why we lost.

380
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,800
That's why Coleen isn't going
to jail.

381
00:21:30,933 --> 00:21:34,200
Look, if you have nothing
good to say,

382
00:21:34,333 --> 00:21:35,333
could you please leave?

383
00:21:35,467 --> 00:21:37,800
I just want to mourn our loss
in this case.

384
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:40,633
Excuse me.

385
00:21:52,667 --> 00:21:55,467
The court has dismissed
the case.

386
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:57,200
Coleen is a free woman.

387
00:21:57,333 --> 00:21:58,767
Really, Attorney?

388
00:21:58,900 --> 00:21:59,900
Yes, Coleen.

389
00:22:00,033 --> 00:22:05,467
The court has decided Timo's
recantation is credible.

390
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:09,933
And there's no more evidence
linking you to the alleged act.

391
00:22:10,067 --> 00:22:12,433
So, case dismissed.

392
00:22:12,567 --> 00:22:14,267
Thank you so much, Attorney!

393
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:16,833
Thank you for all your help.

394
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,900
Mom, I'm not going to jail
anymore!

395
00:22:20,667 --> 00:22:22,267
You're completely free now,
dear.

396
00:22:24,467 --> 00:22:27,900
Attorney, thank you
for the hard work.

397
00:22:28,033 --> 00:22:29,567
Congratulations.

398
00:22:29,700 --> 00:22:30,567
Attorney, congrats.

399
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:31,633
- Thank you.
- I'm just doing my job.

400
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:33,267
Thank you for everything.

401
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:36,633
You know what?
This calls for a celebration.

402
00:22:36,767 --> 00:22:38,667
How about we eat out?

403
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:40,267
Does Dad know yet?

404
00:22:43,233 --> 00:22:45,167
Attorney,

405
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:48,800
does Hazel's side already have
a copy of the dismissal order?

406
00:22:48,967 --> 00:22:50,200
Yeah.

407
00:22:50,333 --> 00:22:51,967
I want to go see Dad.

408
00:22:56,067 --> 00:22:57,367
Dear, you can't.

409
00:22:58,567 --> 00:23:00,433
Why not?

410
00:23:00,567 --> 00:23:02,667
The case is dismissed, right?

411
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,967
Maybe he's not mad at me
anymore.

412
00:23:05,100 --> 00:23:09,567
It was proven that I had nothing
to do with Jessica's death.

413
00:23:10,633 --> 00:23:13,900
Dear, he already knows
that you're innocent.

414
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:17,833
If he knows...

415
00:23:17,967 --> 00:23:20,033
If he believes that...

416
00:23:20,167 --> 00:23:21,867
then why did he leave?

417
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,533
I already did
what you told me to do.

418
00:23:32,667 --> 00:23:36,233
So I hope you'll also keep
your end of the deal.

419
00:23:36,367 --> 00:23:37,933
On one condition.

420
00:23:38,067 --> 00:23:39,400
You accept no visitors.

421
00:23:39,533 --> 00:23:42,767
Especially Coleen
and her family.

422
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:43,933
Timo.

423
00:23:48,367 --> 00:23:50,167
- Dad?
- Hello, Jeffrey, son.

424
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:51,367
How are you?

425
00:23:52,533 --> 00:23:53,400
Manuel?

426
00:23:53,533 --> 00:23:54,567
Manuel?
